  "text": "These optimal positions are, however, substantively closer to the center than are the actual (mean-perceived) positions. Adams and Merrill (1999a, b) and [CITATION_1] argue that models incorporating additional voter-candidate interactions better represent voter preferences and predict much more realistic optimal strategies.",
